ENTRY       EC 1.1.1.239                Enzyme
NAME        3alpha(17beta)-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase (NAD+);
            3alpha,17beta-hydroxy steroid dehydrogenase;
            3alpha(17beta)-HSD;
            17-ketoreductase (ambiguous);
            17beta-HSD (ambiguous);
            HSD17B6 (gene name);
            HSD17B8 (gene name)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     3alpha(or 17beta)-hydroxysteroid:NAD+ oxidoreductase
REACTION    testosterone + NAD+ = androstenedione + NADH + H+ [RN:R01836]
ALL_REAC    R01836
SUBSTRATE   testosterone [CPD:C00535];
            NAD+ [CPD:C00003]
PRODUCT     androstenedione [CPD:C00280];
            NADH [CPD:C00004];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     Also acts on other 17beta-hydroxysteroids and on the 3alpha-hydroxy group of pregnanes and bile acids. Different from EC 1.1.1.50 3alpha-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase (Si-specific) or EC 1.1.1.213 3alpha-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase (Re-specific).
